name: Goodwill Westgate Plaza
directions: Back of the store near the shoes on the left hand side of the store. There will be a hallway there with the bathrooms on the left hand side of the hallway.
comment: Unsure if 100% wheelchair accessible, but are single stalled gendered restrooms. I don't think you have to be a paying customer, but maybe look around a bit to be safe. They had some cool stuff though!

name: Busch gardens
directions: In the very back of the park, there is a food stand called Kenya Kanteen (spelled like that) and in between that and the safari expedition meet up place, there is a bathroom area with a unisex stall labeled “companion restroom”
comment: I didn’t go in it, so I don’t know for sure if there’s a changing table or not. Allegedly there are more in the park but that’s the only one I saw

name: 1925 San Jacinto Blvd, Austin, TX 78712, USA
comment: men’s and women’s restrooms, but UT welcomes gender diversity

name: 185 N Main St, North Canton, OH 44720, USA
directions: Upstairs in the back of the children’s room by the elevators

name: Heb

name: Old Navy
directions: Left side at the Back of store

name: Biopalatset
directions: at the cinema one the second floor
comment: you may need to say in the checkout if they do not let you in

name: Manrique's Mexican Restaurant
directions: When you first walk in the door take a left through the stone archway, and you should see a hallway. Go down the hallway and the bathrooms are on the left side of the hallway.
comment: I do believe you have to be a paying customer, but I would ask the staff. They have single stalled restrooms, and there are no changing tables at least in the men's restroom. I also don't think that it is wheelchair accessible.

name: Campus Dr, Glen Head, NY 11545, USA

name: Regal Cinema Dulles Town Center
directions: On the right going down the hall of theater entrances.  Marked "family" with unisex bathroom sign.
comment: Neutral restroom is beyond ticket taker, must be a paying ticket holder.  Other external restrooms exist but are not gender neutral or single stall.

name: Advanced Teaching and Research Building
directions: First floor, past the student lounge, second door to the left

name: Beecroft Place

comment: It is only one room, and you can only get in if it’s vacant, plus it being a disabled bathroom, so be quick just in case!

name: Target
directions: To the left when you walk in through the mall entrance, right next to the cafe
comment: There are two accessible single-stall restrooms upstairs. From the escalators, walk straight back through the electronics department. They are in an alcove with water fountains. One is designated "unisex family restroom" and has a changing table. The other is designated "mens" and does not have a changing table. Neither require a key/code to access as of 3/2019.

name: Santa Monica Place
directions: Third floor bathrooms include two gender neutral stalls

name: The Imperial Life
directions: Enter then follow the glass to the right, can't miss it
comment: Expensive food and drinks, but nice atmosphere.

name: Zara Hassan

name: Urban Orchard Cider Co.

comment: Paying customer, no minors after 8pm

name: Garden City Collegiate
directions: Beside main office
comment: For students/staff

name: Zachary

comment: This is a tap house with beer. Minors are allowed to order coffee at the coffee bar inside the same building but cannot sit in establishment.

name: Venice Beach Boardwalk

name: Richard J Daley Library

comment: There are two all-gender restrooms. No key/code is required to enter as of 3/2019.

name: Witte museum

name: Starbucks

name: Starbucks
directions: To the right of the shop

name: Speedway
directions: On the far right wall after you walk in, pretty easy to spot.
comment: Also usually pretty clean and well stocked.

name: Great Northern Mall
directions: Find the food court (there are maps or just ask for directions), there should be a sign pointing to the restrooms. On their official website greatnorthernmall.com they have a map of the mall.
comment: The bathroom is called “the family room”, don’t feel embarrassed about using it because everyone who doesn’t want to use gendered bathrooms uses it anyway. So don’t worry you will blend right in.

name: rubios
directions: ground floor towards the back of the building
comment: don’t need to be a paying customer

name: UNI Bookstore

comment: If coming from upstairs, there's an elevator all the way in the back for people with accessibility issues

name: Target
directions: Street level, back left side, off the drink aisle
comment: Bathrooms are locked so you have to ask an employee to let you in.

name: Village park

comment: There are two.

name: Ezequiel
directions: Located near the general area of the Women’s/Men’s restrooms.
comment: There is no baby changing station but there is a small table inside the restroom.

name: Chipotle
directions: 2 bathrooms, both accessible, both single stall, one labelled “men” one labelled “women”. End of hall past food prep area. Discrete.
comment: Easy to just go in and go to bathroom. They sell single bottles of water but there’s a usual waiting line. They usually don’t care if you just use bathroom. :)

name: Fairfield County District Library
directions: Two nongendered single stall restrooms are on the lower level. Take the stairs or take the elevator, turn left once you're downstairs.
comment:
Lower level restrooms are gender neutral, and one is wheelchair accessible and fairly roomy. Both lower level restrooms are single stall and have urinals.
Restrooms on other floors are gendered. All of their restrooms are very clean. The librarians are great people!

directions: On the ground floor, through the visitor area and on the right
comment: Four gender neutral individual toilets. NLS is free to enter, so no need to buy anything etc

In the back beside the counter.
